      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## What's changed\n\n**Raises `minAppVersion` to 0.16.0.** The plugin uses `Workspace.getLeaf(true)` to open imported papers in a new tab, which is annotated `@since 0.16.0` in Obsidian's API. Earlier manifests declared `0.15.0` and the marketplace reviewer flagged this. 0.16.0 shipped in August 2022 and the current Obsidian client is on the 1.x line, so this should not exclude any active users.\n\nThis release also rolls up the lint hygiene work from 1.0.6, which addressed all warnings from the 1.0.5 marketplace review (window timers, typed Promise rejections, replaced `any` in the import modal with a proper discriminated union, etc.).\n\n## Upgrade notes\n\nNo template changes from 1.0.4 — the `{{ALPHAXIV}}` placeholder added in 1.0.4 is still the most recent template change. If you upgraded from before 1.0.4 and customized your note template, you can still add `alphaxiv: {{ALPHAXIV}}` under `url: {{URL}}` in **Settings → Note template** to surface the alphaxiv conversation link in frontmatter.",
