      "author": "Ar4l",
      "description": "## arXiv Papers v1.0.2\n\nFork of [willjhliang/obsidian-papers](https://github.com/willjhliang/obsidian-papers) with arXiv rate-limit handling and OpenAlex fallback.\n\n### Fixes\n- Adds a shared `arxivRequest` helper: rate-limits requests to ≥3s gap (per arXiv's stated policy), wall-clock timeout (10s) to abort arXiv's tarpit, exponential backoff on HTTP 429/503 and consecutive timeouts.\n- Falls back to OpenAlex when arXiv is rate-limiting your IP — common on VPNs, where the shared egress IP eats throttling from the whole pool.\n- Adds an optional **Contact email** setting used as the OpenAlex `mailto=` polite-pool identifier.\n\n### Install\nDownload `main.js`, `manifest.json`, `styles.css` below and drop them into `<vault>/.obsidian/plugins/arxiv-papers/`, then enable in Settings → Community plugins.",
